      • ModifyVirtualNetworkRequest

        @Since(value="7.0")
public ModifyVirtualNetworkRequest(Optional<Long> virtualNetworkID,
                                 Optional<Long> virtualNetworkTag,
                                 Optional<String> name,
                                 Optional<AddressBlock[]> addressBlocks,
                                 Optional<String> netmask,
                                 Optional<String> svip,
                                 Optional<Map<String,Object>> attributes)
        The Request object for the "ModifyVirtualNetwork" API Service call.
        Parameters:
        virtualNetworkID - (optional) Unique identifier of the virtual network to modify. This is the virtual network ID assigned by the SolidFire cluster.
        virtualNetworkTag - (optional) Network Tag that identifies the virtual network to modify.
        name - (optional) New name for the virtual network.
        addressBlocks - (optional) New addressBlock to set for this Virtual Network object. This may contain new address blocks to add to the existing object or it may omit unused address blocks that need to be removed. Alternatively, existing address blocks may be extended or reduced in size. The size of the starting addressBlocks for a Virtual Network object can only be increased, and can never be decreased.
        netmask - (optional) New netmask for this virtual network.
        svip - (optional) The storage virtual IP address for this virtual network. The svip for Virtual Network cannot be changed. A new Virtual Network must be created in order to use a different svip address.
        attributes - (optional) A new list of Name/Value pairs in JSON object format.
        Since:
        7.0

      • getAddressBlocks

        public Optional<AddressBlock[]> getAddressBlocks()
        New addressBlock to set for this Virtual Network object. This may contain new address blocks to add to the existing object or it may omit unused address blocks that need to be removed. Alternatively, existing address blocks may be extended or reduced in size. The size of the starting addressBlocks for a Virtual Network object can only be increased, and can never be decreased. Attributes for this parameter are:
        start: start of the IP address range. (String)
        size: numbre of IP addresses to include in the block. (Integer)
